{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I would like to tell you all"},{"time":2000,"text":"that you are all actually cyborgs,"},{"time":6000,"text":"but not the cyborgs that you think."},{"time":8000,"text":"You're not RoboCop, and you're not Terminator,"},{"time":11000,"text":"but you're cyborgs every time you look at a computer screen"},{"time":13000,"text":"or use one of your cell phone devices."},{"time":16000,"text":"So what's a good definition for cyborg?"},{"time":18000,"text":"Well, traditional definition is \"an organism"},{"time":20000,"text":"to which exogenous components have been added"},{"time":22000,"text":"for the purpose of adapting to new environments.\""},{"time":24000,"text":"That came from a 1960 paper on space travel,"},{"time":27000,"text":"because, if you think about it, space is pretty awkward."},{"time":29000,"text":"People aren't supposed to be there."},{"time":31000,"text":"But humans are curious, and they like to add things to their bodies"},{"time":34000,"text":"so they can go to the Alps one day"},{"time":36000,"text":"and then become a fish in the sea the next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"So let's look at the concept of traditional anthropology."},{"time":41000,"text":"Somebody goes to another country,"},{"time":43000,"text":"says, \"How fascinating these people are, how interesting their tools are,"},{"time":46000,"text":"how curious their culture is.\""},{"time":48000,"text":"And then they write a paper, and maybe a few other anthropologists read it,"},{"time":51000,"text":"and we think it's very exotic."},{"time":53000,"text":"Well, what's happening"},{"time":56000,"text":"is that we've suddenly found a new species."},{"time":59000,"text":"I, as a cyborg anthropologist, have suddenly said,"},{"time":61000,"text":"\"Oh, wow. Now suddenly we're a new form of Homo sapiens,"},{"time":64000,"text":"and look at these fascinating cultures,"},{"time":66000,"text":"and look at these curious rituals"},{"time":68000,"text":"that everybody's doing around this technology."},{"time":70000,"text":"They're clicking on things and staring at screens.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":73000,"text":"Now there's a reason why I study this,"},{"time":75000,"text":"versus traditional anthropology."},{"time":77000,"text":"And the reason is that tool use,"},{"time":79000,"text":"in the beginning -- for thousands and thousands of years,"},{"time":82000,"text":"everything has been a physical modification of self."},{"time":85000,"text":"It has helped us to extend our physical selves,"},{"time":87000,"text":"go faster, hit things harder,"},{"time":89000,"text":"and there's been a limit on that."},{"time":91000,"text":"But now what we're looking at is not an extension of the physical self,"},{"time":94000,"text":"but an extension of the mental self,"},{"time":96000,"text":"and because of that, we're able to travel faster,"},{"time":98000,"text":"communicate differently."},{"time":100000,"text":"And the other thing that happens"},{"time":102000,"text":"is that we're all carrying around little Mary Poppins technology."},{"time":105000,"text":"We can put anything we want into it, and it doesn't get heavier,"},{"time":108000,"text":"and then we can take anything out."},{"time":110000,"text":"What does the inside of your computer actually look like?"},{"time":112000,"text":"Well, if you print it out, it looks like a thousand pounds of material"},{"time":115000,"text":"that you're carrying around all the time."},{"time":117000,"text":"And if you actually lose that information,"},{"time":120000,"text":"it means that you suddenly have this loss in your mind,"},{"time":123000,"text":"that you suddenly feel like something's missing,"},{"time":126000,"text":"except you aren't able to see it, so it feels like a very strange emotion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"The other thing that happens is that you have a second self."},{"time":132000,"text":"Whether you like it or not, you're starting to show up online,"},{"time":134000,"text":"and people are interacting with your second self"},{"time":136000,"text":"when you're not there."},{"time":138000,"text":"And so you have to be careful"},{"time":140000,"text":"about leaving your front lawn open,"},{"time":142000,"text":"which is basically your Facebook wall,"},{"time":144000,"text":"so that people don't write on it in the middle of the night --"},{"time":146000,"text":"because it's very much the equivalent."},{"time":148000,"text":"And suddenly we have to start to maintain our second self."},{"time":151000,"text":"You have to present yourself in digital life"},{"time":153000,"text":"in a similar way that you would in your analog life."},{"time":156000,"text":"So, in the same way that you wake up, take a shower and get dressed,"},{"time":159000,"text":"you have to learn to do that for your digital self."},{"time":161000,"text":"And the problem is that a lot of people now,"},{"time":163000,"text":"especially adolescents,"},{"time":165000,"text":"have to go through two adolescences."},{"time":167000,"text":"They have to go through their primary one, that's already awkward,"},{"time":170000,"text":"and then they go through their second self's adolescence,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and that's even more awkward"},{"time":174000,"text":"because there's an actual history"},{"time":177000,"text":"of what they've gone through online."},{"time":179000,"text":"And anybody coming in new to technology"},{"time":181000,"text":"is an adolescent online right now,"},{"time":183000,"text":"and so it's very awkward,"},{"time":185000,"text":"and it's very difficult for them to do those things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"So when I was little, my dad would sit me down at night and he would say,"},{"time":190000,"text":"\"I'm going to teach you about time and space in the future.\""},{"time":192000,"text":"And I said, \"Great.\""},{"time":194000,"text":"And he said one day, \"What's the shortest distance between two points?\""},{"time":196000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, that's a straight line. You told me that yesterday.\""},{"time":199000,"text":"I thought I was very clever."},{"time":201000,"text":"He said, \"No, no, no. Here's a better way.\""},{"time":204000,"text":"He took a piece of paper,"},{"time":206000,"text":"drew A and B on one side and the other"},{"time":208000,"text":"and folded them together so where A and B touched."},{"time":211000,"text":"And he said, \"That is the shortest distance between two points.\""},{"time":214000,"text":"And I said, \"Dad, dad, dad, how do you do that?\""},{"time":216000,"text":"He said, \"Well, you just bend time and space,"},{"time":218000,"text":"it takes an awful lot of energy,"},{"time":220000,"text":"and that's just how you do it.\""},{"time":222000,"text":"And I said, \"I want to do that.\""},{"time":224000,"text":"And he said, \"Well, okay.\""},{"time":226000,"text":"And so, when I went to sleep for the next 10 or 20 years,"},{"time":229000,"text":"I was thinking at night,"},{"time":231000,"text":"\"I want to be the first person to create a wormhole,"},{"time":233000,"text":"to make things accelerate faster."},{"time":235000,"text":"And I want to make a time machine.\""},{"time":237000,"text":"I was always sending messages to my future self"},{"time":239000,"text":"using tape recorders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"But then what I realized when I went to college"},{"time":246000,"text":"is that technology doesn't just get adopted"},{"time":248000,"text":"because it works."},{"time":250000,"text":"It gets adopted because people use it"},{"time":252000,"text":"and it's made for humans."},{"time":254000,"text":"So I started studying anthropology."},{"time":256000,"text":"And when I was writing my thesis on cell phones,"},{"time":258000,"text":"I realized that everyone was carrying around wormholes in their pockets."},{"time":261000,"text":"They weren't physically transporting themselves;"},{"time":263000,"text":"they were mentally transporting themselves."},{"time":265000,"text":"They would click on a button,"},{"time":267000,"text":"and they would be connected as A to B immediately."},{"time":270000,"text":"And I thought, \"Oh, wow. I found it. This is great.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"So over time, time and space"},{"time":274000,"text":"have compressed because of this."},{"time":276000,"text":"You can stand on one side of the world,"},{"time":278000,"text":"whisper something and be heard on the other."},{"time":280000,"text":"One of the other ideas that comes around"},{"time":282000,"text":"is that you have a different type of time on every single device that you use."},{"time":285000,"text":"Every single browser tab gives you a different type of time."},{"time":288000,"text":"And because of that, you start to dig around"},{"time":290000,"text":"for your external memories -- where did you leave them?"},{"time":292000,"text":"So now we're all these paleontologists"},{"time":294000,"text":"that are digging for things that we've lost"},{"time":296000,"text":"on our external brains that we're carrying around in our pockets."},{"time":299000,"text":"And that incites a sort of panic architecture --"},{"time":301000,"text":"\"Oh no, where's this thing?\""},{"time":303000,"text":"We're all \"I Love Lucy\" on a great assembly line of information,"},{"time":306000,"text":"and we can't keep up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"And so what happens is,"},{"time":311000,"text":"when we bring all that into the social space,"},{"time":313000,"text":"we end up checking our phones all the time."},{"time":315000,"text":"So we have this thing called ambient intimacy."},{"time":317000,"text":"It's not that we're always connected to everybody,"},{"time":319000,"text":"but at anytime we can connect to anyone we want."},{"time":322000,"text":"And if you were able to print out everybody in your cell phone,"},{"time":324000,"text":"the room would be very crowded."},{"time":326000,"text":"These are the people that you have access to right now, in general --"},{"time":329000,"text":"all of these people, all of your friends and family that you can connect to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"And so there are some psychological effects that happen with this."},{"time":335000,"text":"One I'm really worried about"},{"time":337000,"text":"is that people aren't taking time for mental reflection anymore,"},{"time":340000,"text":"and that they aren't slowing down and stopping,"},{"time":342000,"text":"being around all those people in the room all the time"},{"time":344000,"text":"that are trying to compete for their attention"},{"time":346000,"text":"on the simultaneous time interfaces,"},{"time":348000,"text":"paleontology and panic architecture."},{"time":350000,"text":"They're not just sitting there."},{"time":352000,"text":"And really, when you have no external input,"},{"time":355000,"text":"that is a time when there is a creation of self,"},{"time":357000,"text":"when you can do long-term planning,"},{"time":359000,"text":"when you can try and figure out who you really are."},{"time":362000,"text":"And then, once you do that, you can figure out"},{"time":364000,"text":"how to present your second self in a legitimate way,"},{"time":366000,"text":"instead of just dealing with everything as it comes in --"},{"time":368000,"text":"and oh, I have to do this, and I have to do this, and I have to do this."},{"time":371000,"text":"And so this is very important."},{"time":373000,"text":"I'm really worried that, especially kids today,"},{"time":375000,"text":"they're not going to be dealing with this down-time,"},{"time":378000,"text":"that they have an instantaneous button-clicking culture,"},{"time":380000,"text":"and that everything comes to them,"},{"time":382000,"text":"and that they become very excited about it and very addicted to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"So if you think about it, the world hasn't stopped either."},{"time":388000,"text":"It has its own external prosthetic devices,"},{"time":390000,"text":"and these devices are helping us all"},{"time":392000,"text":"to communicate and interact with each other."},{"time":394000,"text":"But when you actually visualize it,"},{"time":396000,"text":"all the connections that we're doing right now --"},{"time":398000,"text":"this is an image of the mapping of the Internet --"},{"time":401000,"text":"it doesn't look technological."},{"time":403000,"text":"It actually looks very organic."},{"time":405000,"text":"This is the first time in the entire history of humanity"},{"time":408000,"text":"that we've connected in this way."},{"time":411000,"text":"And it's not that machines are taking over."},{"time":414000,"text":"It's that they're helping us to be more human,"},{"time":416000,"text":"helping us to connect with each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"The most successful technology gets out of the way"},{"time":421000,"text":"and helps us live our lives."},{"time":423000,"text":"And really,"},{"time":425000,"text":"it ends up being more human than technology,"},{"time":428000,"text":"because we're co-creating each other all the time."},{"time":430000,"text":"And so this is the important point that I like to study:"},{"time":433000,"text":"that things are beautiful, that it's still a human connection --"},{"time":436000,"text":"it's just done in a different way."},{"time":438000,"text":"We're just increasing our humanness"},{"time":440000,"text":"and our ability to connect with each other, regardless of geography."},{"time":443000,"text":"So that's why I study cyborg anthropology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}